Radisson Blu Hotel, London Leicester Square

editorialSummary.text: Fixed-price & a la carte French-Mediterranean meals in a sophisticated space at The Londoner hotel.

text.text: People say this restaurant serves delicious Mediterranean cuisine, including baked cod, crispy sea bass, and a standout Sunday roast. They highlight the good value, especially for the set menu, and the relaxed, spacious, and classy atmosphere. They also like the attentive, friendly, and professional service.

originalText.text:
Absolutely amazing experience at Whitcomb’s, London! The lamb Sunday roast was incredible — tender, juicy, and full of flavour — and the steak was honestly one of the best I’ve ever had.

The service was outstanding. Ripon was so friendly and professional, making sure everything was perfect. A huge thank you to Gabi, the lovely Italian waitress, who made us feel so welcome and looked after us beautifully.

Everything from start to finish was just perfect — delicious food, great atmosphere, and top-notch service. Highly recommend Whitcomb’s for anyone looking for a special meal in London!

originalText.text: Had the best dinner experience at Whitcomb’s! The cocktails were expertly made and the steak were delicious. Our waiter Eliza was very attentive and gave us a very good service. Highly recommended!

originalText.text: Went here on a lark and hungry, left full and impressed. The restaurant was not as busy on Friday night after 7pm as expected, particularly considering how good the food and service was. The waitress was friendly, helpful in dialing in dish selections, and the food was fresh, delicious and well-portioned. A very nice experience!

originalText.text:
Great food experience.
The food was absolutely delicious and cooked with perfection.
The menu may seem short but believe me - you don't need more. Great wine selection and the staff are happy to pair the wine for you if you're not sure.
Unfortunately due to a bit long wait for the meals we ran out of time to try desserts.
The staff was very professional and friendly, they made us aware that the awaiting time for meals may be a bit longer.
The place is nice however the tables are very close to each other and it can be a bit loud when it's busy.
